<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1113628-has-anyone-noticed-how-isherwood-uses">Has anyone noticed how Isherwood uses point of view in the book? Some things that I noticed are how, at only one point, he gets into another character&#39;s head, George&#39;s neighbor&#39;s--&quot;Poor man, she thinks, living there all alone. He has a kind face.&quot; Other than that, it seems to be third-person close to George all the time. Then, there is the use of &quot;we&quot;--&quot;We see the face relax.&quot; Isherwood is talking to us!</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
